    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @caybro - have discussed with the design team - the consensus is not to address this at this point but we will of course consider it for the redesign. \r\n\r\nThe rationale for that is that the user can see very little of the message in this scenario, so they are unlikely to want to access the message contextual controls. If they have an interest in performing an action on the message they are likely to scroll up until it is more visible so they can ensure they are performing the action on the correct message. By that point, the flyout will be fully visible given the flyout is anchored to the top of the message.\r\n\r\nHope that works for you! Any issues just shout.",
